{\footnote # IDH_MODULA3_20}
{\footnote $ Modula-3 - INFLUENCE}
{\footnote K Modula-3 influence;Java;C#;Python;Go;comparaison Modula-2}
\b\fs24 INFLUENCE \b0\fs20\par
\par
Modula-3 a directement influence :\par
\par
{\f1   - Java (1995)   : objets traces+GC, exceptions, threads,}\par
{\f1                     interfaces, generiques (plus tard)}\par
{\f1   - C# (2000)     : structure du langage, exceptions,}\par
{\f1                     delegates (procedures-types)}\par
{\f1   - Python        : exceptions}\par
{\f1   - Go (2009)     : modularite stricte, simplicite,}\par
{\f1                     importation explicite}\par
\par
Comparaison Modula-3 / Modula-2 :\par
\par
{\f1   Aspect          Modula-2          Modula-3}\par
{\f1   ------          --------          --------}\par
{\f1   Objets          non               OBJECT/METHODS/OVERRIDES}\par
{\f1   Exceptions      non               TRY/EXCEPT/FINALLY/RAISE}\par
{\f1   Threads         coroutines        Thread/Mutex/Condition}\par
{\f1   GC              non               oui (REF traces)}\par
{\f1   Generiques     non               GENERIC INTERFACE/MODULE}\par
{\f1   Interfaces      DEFINITION MODULE INTERFACE}\par
{\f1   Type opaque     limite            <: REFANY + REVEAL}\par
{\f1   Cast            CAST              LOOPHOLE (UNSAFE)}\par
{\f1   Unsafe          partout           isole UNSAFE INTERFACE}\par
{\f1   TEXT            ARRAY OF CHAR     type TEXT immuable+GC}\par
\par
